arles schwab corporation from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search for people named charles schwab including the founder of this company see charles schwab disambiguation the charles schwab corporation type public company traded as nyse schw sp  component industry financial services founded april  as first commander corporation founder charles schwab headquarters san francisco california number of locations  branches key people charles schwab chairman walt bettinger president and ceo services brokerage firm revenue us billion  net income us billion  total assets us billion  total equity us billion  number of employees  website wwwschwabcom the charles schwab corporation is a bank and brokerage firm based in san francisco california it was founded in  by charles r schwab it is on the list of largest banks in the united states and is one of the largest brokerage firms in the united states the company provides services for individuals and institutions that are investing online the company offers an electronic trading platform for the purchase and sale of financial securities including common stocks preferred stocks futures contracts exchangetraded funds options mutual funds and fixed income investments it also provides margin lending and cash management services the company also provides services through registered investment advisers contents  current operations  history  marketing  schwab charitable fund  see also  references  further reading  external links current operationsedit schwab operates in four main divisions investing wealth management banking and trading as of december   the company had  million active client brokerage accounts with  trillion in assets the company operated  branches in  states as well as a branch in each of puerto rico and london historyedit in  charles r schwab and two other partners launched investment indicator an investment newsletter at its height the newsletter had  subscribers each paying  a year to subscribe in april  the firm was incorporated in california as first commander corporation a wholly owned subsidiary of commander industries inc for traditional brokerage services and to publish the schwab investment newsletter in november of that year mr schwab and four others purchased all the stock from commander industries inc and in  mr schwab bought all the stock from what was once commander industries in  the company name changed to charles schwab  co inc in  the us securities and exchange commission allowed for negotiated commission rates and schwab set up a discount brokerage in september  schwab opened its first branch in sacramento ca and started offering discount brokerage services in  schwab began offering seminars to clients and by  schwab had  client accounts total doubling to  in  in  schwab established the industry’s first hour quotation service and the total of client accounts grew to  in  schwab became a member of the nyse and the total of client accounts grew to  in  schwab became the first to offer  order entry and quote service its first international office was opened in hong kong and the number of client accounts totaled  in  the company was purchased by bank of america for  million in  the company launched  noload mutual funds in  management including charles r schwab bought the company from bank of america for  million in  the company acquired mayer  scweitzer a market making firm allowing schwab to execute its customers orders without sending them to an exchange in  it was fined  for failing to arrange the best trades for its customers the unit was renamed schwab capital markets in  in  the company opened an office in london in  the company acquired the hampton company founded by walter w bettinger who became ceo of schwab in  in  schwab purchased us trust for  billion in  less than a year after the acquisition of us trust the us trust subsidiary was fined  million in a bank secrecy law case it was ordered to pay  million to the new york state bankin