 an ultra short bond fund schwab marketed the fund as a cash equivalent investment and as a safe alternative to money market funds with a higher yield and only slightly more risk such a claim would be incorrect for a typical conventionally managed ultra short bond fund but was especially false when made by schwab on behalf of the yieldplus fund in its marketing materials schwab compared returns on the yieldplus fund to returns on the lehman short us treasury  month index the treasury securities included in the lehman index have no credit risk are highly liquid and have short maturities the holdings of the yieldplus fund generally shared none of these attributes  yieldplus had  billion of investor losses including losses by the founder himself schwab closed the yieldplus funds in   in  the company acquired the k company on july   walter w bettinger the previous chief operating officer was named chief executive succeeding the companys namesake charles r schwab remained executive chairman of the company and said in a statement that he would continue to serve as a very active chairman bettinger stated chuck and i have worked closely together over the years preparing for this transition and we will continue to work closely together in our respective roles as executive chairman and ceo in  the company acquired optionsxpress in  the company acquired thomaspartners an asset management firm marketingedit in  havas worldwide then called euro rscg was chosen by charles schwab as its fullservice advertising agency in february  schwab announced that they had hired crispin porter  bogusky cpb as their lead creative agency with havas worldwide remaining to create ads for activetrader and optionsxpress in march  adweek reported on marketing material created by cpb for schwabs intelligent portfolio service starting in  the company launched a series of television ads featuring the slogan talk to chuck the tv ads were produced by havas worldwide then called euro rscg and directedanima