ng  external links current operationsedit schwab operates in four main divisions investing wealth management banking and trading as of december   the company had  million active client brokerage accounts with  trillion in assets the company operated  branches in  states as well as a branch in each of puerto rico and london historyedit in  charles r schwab and two other partners launched investment indicator an investment newsletter at its height the newsletter had  subscribers each paying  a year to subscribe in april  the firm was incorporated in california as first commander corporation a wholly owned subsidiary of commander industries inc for traditional brokerage services and to publish the schwab investment newsletter in november of that year mr schwab and four others purchased all the stock from commander industries inc and in  mr schwab bought all the stock from what was once commander industries in  the company name changed to charles schwab  co inc in  the us securities and exchange commission allowed for negotiated commission rates and schwab set up a discount brokerage in september  schwab opened its first branch in sacramento ca and started offering discount brokerage services in  schwab began offering seminars to clients and by  schwab had  client accounts total doubling to  in  in  schwab established the industry’s first hour quotation service and the total of client accounts grew to  in  schwab became a member of the nyse and the total of client accounts grew to  in  schwab became the first to offer  order entry and quote service its first international office was opened in hong kong and the number of client accounts totaled  in  the company was purchased by bank of america for  million in  the company launched  noload mutual funds in  management including charles r schwab bought the company from bank of america for  million in  the company acquired mayer  scweitzer a market making firm allowing schwab to execute its customers orders without sending t