es in four main divisions investing wealth management banking and trading as of december   the company had  million active client brokerage accounts with  trillion in assets the company operated  branches in  states as well as a branch in each of puerto rico and london historyedit in  charles r schwab and two other partners launched investment indicator an investment newsletter at its height the newsletter had  subscribers each paying  a year to subscribe in april  the firm was incorporated in california as first commander corporation a wholly owned subsidiary of commander industries inc for traditional brokerage services and to publish the schwab investment newsletter in november of that year mr schwab and four others purchased all the stock from commander industries inc and in  mr schwab bought all the stock from what was once commander industries in  the company name changed to charles schwab  co inc in  the us securities and exchange commission allowed for negotiated commission rates and schwab set up a discount brokerage in september  schwab opened its first branch in sacramento ca and started offering discount brokerage services in  schwab began offering seminars to clients and by  schwab had  client accounts total doubling to  in  in  schwab established the industry’s first hour quotation service and the total of client accounts grew to  in  schwab became a member of the nyse and the total of client accounts grew to  in  schwab became the first to offer  order entry and quote service its first international office was opened in hong kong and the number of client accounts totaled  in  the company was purchased by bank of america for  million in  the company launched  noload mutual funds in  management including charles r schwab bought the company from bank of america for  million in  the company acquired mayer  scweitzer a market making firm allowing schwab to execute its customers orders without sending them to an exchange in  it was fined  for failing to arrange the best trades for its customers the unit was renamed schwab capital markets in  in  the company opened an office in london in  the company acquired the hampton company founded by walter w bettinger who became ceo of schwab in  in  schwab purchased us trust for  billion in  less than a year after the acquisition of us trust the us trust subsidiary was fined  million in a bank secrecy law case it was ordered to pay  million to the new york state banking department and  million to the federal reserve board on november   schwab announced an agreement to sell us trust to bank of america for  billion in cash the deal closed in the second quarter of  in november  schwab announced the  million acquisition of soundview technology group to add equity research capabilities david s pottruck who had spent the majority of his  years at the brokerage as charles r schwabs righthand man shared the ceo title with the companys founder from  to  in may  mr schwab stepped down and gave pottruck sole control as ceo on july   the companys board fired pottruck replacing him with its founder and namesake news of pottrucks removal came as the firm had announced that overall profit had dropped  percent to  million for the second quarter driven largely by a  percent decline in revenue from customer stock trading after coming back into control mr schwab conceded that the company had lost touch with our heritage and quickly refocused the business on providing financial advice to individual investors he also rolled back pottruck’s fee hikes the company rebounded and earnings began to turn around in  as did the stock the share price was up as high as  since pottruck’s removal ten times since the return of charles schwab the company’s net transfer assets or assets that come from other firms quadrupled from  to  schwab yieldplus fund this fund was named as one of the decades top ten fund disasters for the s “in written materials and in conversations with customers some schwab representatives 